This paper involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques to extract and analyse named entities from news articles. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves unsupervised analysis of large amounts of data, which could also fit into Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also involves building a knowledge base, which could fit into the sub-categories of Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper involves visualisation techniques, which could fit into the sub-category of Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD).
